channel.title: If you get this...he sent another
channel.description:
some kid sent this to me because he is a idiot... if you get it in a pm dont use it it has viruses [quote="KwiKStan"]With new updates, come new glitches. This one is no exception, but this glitch is immensely large. In the museum, you can gain lamps that will up your XP in a chosen skill by 1k, or 10k xp. Jagex seem to have handled the item creation incorrectly, resulting in the following glitch. DIGSITE QUEST IS REQUIRED. (EASY, SHORT QUEST)
In the museum, stand in THIS spot:
[IMG]http://i19.tinypic.com/4ulem9w.png[/img]
When you are there, set the amount of lamps you wish to create using the + and - buttons. Click whether you wish to create 10k xp or 1k xp lamps.
Do not create more than 28 lamps at once, as this will usually result in you disconnecting from Runescape. I'll fix this later.
THIS PROGRAM IS NEWLY MADE, PLEASE REPORT ANY BUGS TO ME.
link removed
- Stan
http://www.kwickfix.org <lhso3@msn.com>[/quote]
[quote="Valde11"]Yesterday, Jagex updated varrock and the museum. Inside the museum there is a new minigame where it is possible to obtain lamps that raise your XP by 1K or 10K.
We at KwickFix released a program to spawn these lamps, which to our best knowledge worked in MOST cases due to a glitch that Jagex will most likely fix in a few updates time. However, we have now finalised the 100% working program and are releasing it to the public with a short guide. This will most likely not work for long as Jagex are quick to fix bugs.
Firstly, you need to be standing AROUND the gate in the museum, as shown here:
[IMG]http://i16.tinypic.com/6b3tp28.png[/img]
Then, simply scroll to select how many lamps you wish to make, and VOILA! They will appear under your feet. Then you can simply use them to raise the skill of your choice!
[IMG]http://i16.tinypic.com/5xy2g6s.png[/img]
[IMG]http://i7.tinypic.com/626j3lw.png[/img]
If the program doesn't work, run a test to check the connection. If it fails then make sure it is cleared for access by your firewall.
[IMG]http://i8.tinypic.com/6b2myxu.png[/img]
-------------
Downloadable at link removed[/quote]
